From the results of the quintile analysis, the SDGs that were the normative responsibility of fewer than 7 agencies were grouped into the Q1 category (very low level of attention), while those SDGs that were officially served by more than 21 agencies were grouped into the Q5 category (very high level of attention; Table 3
                        ). Analyzing the normative framework allows us to visualize the differences in institutional responsibilities and the attention paid to the SDGs. For example, PEMEX (hydrocarbon sector) is responsible for up to 11 SDGs, whereas the Secretary of Public Functions is responsible for two SDGs (Fig. 4
                        ).
